title: The Folly Of Gamer Boycotts (The Jimquisition)
tags: The Jimquisition|Jimquisition|Jim Sterling|Commentary|Criticism|Games|Game|Gamer|Gaming|Videogame|Video Game|Pok√©mon|Pokemon Sword|Pokemon Shield|Sword & Shield|Pokemon Sword and Shield|Nintendo|The Pokemon Company|Game Freak|Nintendo Switch|Boycott|Gamer Boycott|Modern Warfare 2|Call of Duty|Left 4 Dead|Left 4 Dead 2|The Wind Waker|Zelda|Outrage|Controversy|Community|Star Wars Battlefront 2|FPS|RPG|Action|Action Game|Twitter|Social Media
description: http://www.patreon.com/jimquisitionhttp://www.thejimquisition.comhttps://www.thejimporium.comPok√©mon Sword & Shield shifted over 16 million units worldwide despite a significant amount of pre-release controversy. Angry older fans may have promised a boycott, but the game's success has rendered much of the backlash over Dexit rather toothless. This is because Gamer Boycotts don't really work, and the concept has been so thoroughly discredited after years of failed attempts that it invites mockery and overshadows any legitimate complaints or grievances. From Modern Warfare 2 to The Wind Waker, whenever The Gamers(tm) decide not to buy something, that thing gets bought. A lot. description: A man reminisces about the love of his life with a little help from Google. See something in this story you want to try for yourself? Here are a few tips to get you started. First you‚Äôll need the Google Assistant. If you don‚Äôt already have it, you can learn more at https://assistant.google.com00:12 ‚ÄúShow me photos of me and Loretta‚Äù To use the Assistant to pull up photos, make sure you and your favorite people are tagged in your Google Photos. Then just say, ‚ÄúHey Google, show me photos of me and [their name]‚Äù 00:21 ‚ÄúRemember, Loretta hated my mustache.‚ÄùTo try this one, just say, ‚ÄúHey Google, remember‚Ä¶‚Äù and then whatever you‚Äôd like the Assistant to help you recall later. Like ‚ÄúHey Google, remember Dad‚Äôs shoe size is 8 and half‚Äù or ‚Äúremember Maria loves lilies.‚Äù  Then, to see everything you‚Äôve asked the Assistant to remember, just say, ‚ÄúHey Google, what did I tell you to remember?‚Äù00:39 ‚ÄúShow me photos from our anniversary‚ÄùTo see photos from a wedding, anniversary, birthday, or graduation, you‚Äôll need a Google Photos account, and you‚Äôll also need to tell your Assistant the specific date. Just say something like, ‚ÄúHey Google, remember my anniversary is May 18th‚Äù or ‚Äúremember Mark‚Äôs birthday is March 30th.‚Äù Then you can use that information in many ways, like ‚ÄúHey Google, show me photos from our anniversary‚Äù or ‚ÄúHey Google, remind me to buy flowers on Mark‚Äôs birthday.‚Äù00:51 ‚ÄúPlay our favorite movie.‚ÄùFirst, tell your Google Assistant what your favorite movie is by saying, ‚ÄúHey Google, our favorite movie is Casablanca.‚Äù Once you‚Äôve purchased your favorite movie on Google Play Movies or YouTube, all you have to say is, ‚ÄúHey Google, play our favorite movie‚Äù and the movie will start playing.C R E D I T S Voiced by Grandpop Music: Say Something (instrumental) - A Great Big WorldFilm clip: Casablanca. Summer 2020 is the time for F9, the ninth chapter in the saga that has endured for almost two decades and has earned more than $5 billion around the world.  Vin Diesel‚Äôs Dom Toretto is leading a quiet life off the grid with Letty and his son, little Brian, but they know that danger always lurks just over their peaceful horizon. This time, that threat will force Dom to confront the sins of his past if he‚Äôs going to save those he loves most. His crew joins together to stop a world-shattering plot led by the most skilled assassin and high-performance driver they‚Äôve ever encountered: a man who also happens to be Dom‚Äôs forsaken brother, Jakob (John Cena, next year‚Äôs The Suicide Squad). F9 sees the return of Justin Lin as director, who helmed the third, fourth, fifth and sixth chapters of the series when it transformed into a global blockbuster. The action hurtles around the globe‚Äîfrom London to Tokyo, from Central America to Edinburgh, and from a secret bunker in Azerbaijan to the teeming streets of Tblisi. Along the way, old friends will be resurrected, old foes will return, history will be rewritten, and the true meaning of family will be tested like never before.  The film stars returning cast members Michelle Rodriguez, Tyrese Gibson, Chris ‚ÄúLudacris‚Äù Bridges, Jordana Brewster, Nathalie Emmanuel and Sung Kang, with Oscar¬Æ winner Helen Mirren and Oscar¬Æ winner Charlize Theron. F9 also features Grammy-winning superstar Cardi B as new franchise character Leysa, a woman with a connection to Dom‚Äôs past, and a cameo by Reggaeton sensation Ozuna.  F9 is produced by Neal H. description: The World Health Organization is meeting to decide whether the spread of the Wuhan coronavirus amounts to a global health emergency. The virus has now spread to India and Philippines. Thousands of people have been infected worldwide, the vast majority of them in China. Hundreds of foreign nationals are being evacuated from the Chinese city of Wuhan, the epicenter of the coronavirus outbreak. Japan has begun repatriating its citizens, and the US and South Korea are working to move their citizens out of China. More cases of the virus have been confirmed in China. Australia says its citizens who are being brought home from China will be quarantined offshore on Christmas Island at first. Some airlines, including British Airways, have suspended all flights to and from China. In Germany, three new cases have been reported.
